Flexible location within Australia along with work from home options and
Initial 12-month fixed term contract available to suitable candidates with
options for extension.

Your role will include many of the following duties:

Undertake hydrologic modelling including SDL adjustments, Water Sharing Plan
accreditation, compliance and auditing using models of river systems.

Undertake technical studies for assessing impacts of policy options on various
water users in the system.

Carryout modifications and improvements in capabilities of the hydrologic
models (e.g. programming in FORTRAN/Visual C#/Visual Basic/Python) to enable
new water resource management options and policies to be examined.

Prepare reports, technical manuals and presentation of results and analysis in
formats suitable for a range of audiences including Project Boards, technical
working groups, community reference panels, river operators and the general
public.

Contribute and work as part of multidisciplinary project teams.

